//@ compile-fail
//@ error-contains: cannot infer the type parameter

// A generic call where nothing pins a parameter the result mentions used to sail
// through the checker and die in codegen -- "internal error: type variable 'T reached
// codegen" (formerly TODO #5). It is a checker error now, named for what it is: not a
// mismatch, an inference failure, with the repairs spelled out (turbofish, or use the
// result where its type is known).
//
// The detection is deferred: `solve_generics` legitimately fails to pin parameters on
// its probing pass -- `map::set(map::new(), k, v)` solves the inner `new` only when
// the second pass supplies the expected type -- so an unsolved sighting is a
// candidate, promoted to an error only when the expression's FINAL recorded type
// still carries the variable. The annotated and turbofish spellings of this same call
// infer fine and are pinned across the collections corpus.

use std::collections::list;

fn make[T]() -> List[T] { list::new() }

fn main() {
    let a = make();
}
